iSD-TH Client 
------------------

v0.01

Introduction: This is a client for the iServer type of products that record humidity and temperature.

Conf file:
The path for the conf file is /etc/newport/isd_th_client.conf and the syntax of the file is:
IP address
port numner
sampling rate
command

Put this information in the file and then you can log your data by running the command as follows:
$isd_th_client > log.csv &

The client will keep on running and collecting data.

Note: Put isd_th_client executable in the /usr/bin directory before executing the command.
